---
// Internal type specimen — not linked from anywhere. Candidates for the three
// voices (Phase 6). All faces are OFL-licensed, self-hosted via Fontsource.
// Fonts load ONLY on this page; the rest of the site stays on system stacks
// until the decision is made.
import "@fontsource-variable/newsreader";
import "@fontsource-variable/source-serif-4";
import "@fontsource-variable/geist";
import "@fontsource-variable/geist-mono";
import "@fontsource-variable/jetbrains-mono";
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Base title="Type specimen (internal) · Sahil Gaji">
  <Header />
  <main>
    <h1>Type specimen</h1>
    <p class="howto">
      Internal page. Deciding the three voices: serif (display), sans (text),
      mono (data). Judge on phone and desktop, light and dark theme, at arm's
      length. All copy below is real site copy.
    </p>

    <section>
      <h2>1 · Display serif — candidate A: Newsreader</h2>
      <p class="display newsreader">I build systems that keep working when I leave the room.</p>
      <blockquote class="quote newsreader">
        The biggest lesson was that better decisions matter more than more automation.
      </blockquote>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>1 · Display serif — candidate B: Source Serif 4</h2>
      <p class="display sourceserif">I build systems that keep working when I leave the room.</p>
      <blockquote class="quote sourceserif">
        The biggest lesson was that better decisions matter more than more automation.
      </blockquote>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>2 · Text sans — candidate A: Geist</h2>
      <p class="body geist">
        People usually come to me when something feels disorganized or unclear.
        Whether it's a spreadsheet, a workflow, a process, or documentation, I
        start asking questions, breaking things into smaller parts, identifying
        dependencies, and looking for ways to make the system easier to
        understand and maintain. I don't think people come to me because I
        always have the answer — they come because I'm patient enough to
        understand the problem before trying to solve it.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>2 · Text sans — candidate B: system stack</h2>
      <p class="body">
        People usually come to me when something feels disorganized or unclear.
        Whether it's a spreadsheet, a workflow, a process, or documentation, I
        start asking questions, breaking things into smaller parts, identifying
        dependencies, and looking for ways to make the system easier to
        understand and maintain. I don't think people come to me because I
        always have the answer — they come because I'm patient enough to
        understand the problem before trying to solve it.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>3 · Data mono — candidate A: Geist Mono</h2>
      <div class="mono geistmono">
        <p><span class="accent">v0.2.0</span> 2026-07-15 — type &amp; rhythm</p>
        <p>time per application &lt; 30 min · daily search effort 2 h → 10 min</p>
        <p>Hamburg, 2025 · last updated 2026-07-15</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>3 · Data mono — candidate B: JetBrains Mono</h2>
      <div class="mono jetbrains">
        <p><span class="accent">v0.2.0</span> 2026-07-15 — type &amp; rhythm</p>
        <p>time per application &lt; 30 min · daily search effort 2 h → 10 min</p>
        <p>Hamburg, 2025 · last updated 2026-07-15</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>

<style>
  main {
    max-width: var(--measure-prose);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-8) var(--space-3);
  }
  h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-1);
  }
  .howto {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-6);
  }
  section {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-line);
    padding: var(--space-4) 0;
  }
  h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);
  }
  .display {
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);
  }
  .quote {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: var(--space-3);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
  }
  .body {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .mono p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-1);
  }
  .accent {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .newsreader {
    font-family: "Newsreader Variable", Georgia, serif;
  }
  .sourceserif {
    font-family: "Source Serif 4 Variable", Georgia, serif;
  }
  .geist {
    font-family: "Geist Variable", system-ui, sans-serif;
  }
  .geistmono {
    font-family: "Geist Mono Variable", Consolas, monospace;
  }
  .jetbrains {
    font-family: "JetBrains Mono Variable", Consolas, monospace;
  }
</style>
